subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
.

— Reddish-brown, impunctate. Antennae entirely black and only the first basal antennomeres usually contrasting reddish-brown (
Fig. 31
). Ratio length of second to third antennomere 0.80–0.83 (mean: 0.81); ratio length of third to fourth antennomere 0.42–0.46 (mean: 0.44; 
Fig. 32
).
